Dobrzykowo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Barciany, within Kętrzyn County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia. It lies approximately  north-west of Barciany,  north-west of Kętrzyn, and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
